{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-142","title":"尊敬敬畏","sectionId":"chapter-07","sectionTitle":"喜怒哀乐听你说","pageStart":719,"pageEnd":723,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":18,"duplicateEntryCount":13,"pages":[{"number":719,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"142 尊敬敬畏"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"honour [ˈɒnə(r)]","headword":"honour"},{"type":"definition","text":"n./v.尊敬"},{"type":"note","text":"◎in one's honour对…表示尊敬"},{"type":"entry","text":"admiration [ˌædməˈreɪʃn]","headword":"admiration"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.钦佩"},{"type":"note","text":"◎express admiration for对…表示钦佩"},{"type":"entry","text":"regard [rɪˈɡɑːd]","headword":"regard"},{"type":"definition","text":"n./v.尊重，尊敬"},{"type":"note","text":"◎have a high regard for对…高度尊重"},{"type":"entry","text":"reverence [ˈrevərəns]","headword":"reverence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n./v.尊敬"},{"type":"note","text":"◎with reverence诚惶诚恐"},{"type":"entry","text":"veneration [ˌvenəˈreɪʃn]","headword":"veneration"}]},{"number":720,"blocks":[{"type":"definition","text":"n.尊敬，崇拜"},{"type":"note","text":"◎the veneration for对…的崇敬"},{"type":"entry","text":"respectable [rɪˈspektəbl]","headword":"respectable"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.值得尊敬的；正派的，高尚的"},{"type":"note","text":"◎respectable teacher可敬的老师"},{"type":"entry","text":"respectful [rɪˈspektfl]","headword":"respectful"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.恭敬的；充满敬意的"},{"type":"note","text":"◎respectful behavior有礼貌的行为"},{"type":"entry","text":"honorable [ˈɒnərəbl]","headword":"honorable"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.可敬的"}]},{"number":721,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"revered [rɪˈvɪəd]","headword":"revered"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.尊敬的"},{"type":"entry","text":"one's heart谦恭","headword":"one's heart"},{"type":"entry","text":"worshipful [ˈwɜːʃɪpfl]","headword":"worshipful"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.尊敬的"},{"type":"entry","text":"courtly [ˈkɔːtli]","headword":"courtly"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.温文尔雅的"},{"type":"entry","text":"courteously [ˈkɜːtiəsli]","headword":"courteously"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad. 有礼貌地，客气地"},{"type":"entry","text":"be held in high esteem深受敬重","headword":"be held in high esteem"}]},{"number":722,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"look up to 尊敬","headword":"look up to"},{"type":"entry","text":"owe much to 对…深表感激","headword":"owe much to"},{"type":"entry","text":"worth one's salt 名副其实","headword":"worth one's salt"},{"type":"entry","text":"bow in 恭敬","headword":"bow in"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 1"},{"type":"example","text":"A：A father's love is something to cherish and respect.（父爱是值得"},{"type":"text","text":"珍惜和尊敬的。）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：Not when the father is an alcoholic.（当父亲是个酒鬼的时候就"},{"type":"text","text":"不是了。）"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 2"},{"type":"example","text":"A：We owe much to you for your support.（我们对你们的支持深表"},{"type":"text","text":"感激。）"}]},{"number":723,"blocks":[{"type":"example","text":"B：You are welcome. （别客气。）"}]}]}